This paper deals with wireless powered sensor networks (WPSNs) and their optimization, which involves information theory (IT) and network infrastructure (NI). The paper also discusses the use of space division multiple access (SDMA) and time division multiple access (TDMA), which are related to system and control (SY). Additionally, the paper mentions simulations, which could fall under multimedia (MM) or distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (DC).
